Venter (
Fig. 9
). Sternal shield not visible. Ventri­anal shield with no pre­anal setae or pores. Membrane surrounding ventri­anal shield with 3 pairs of setae and 1 pair of oblong poroids; ventri­anal shield 50 long, 42 wide at level of anterior corners and 35 wide at level of anus. Setae JV 5 transversely aligned with posterior margin of anus.

The position of seta JV 5 is very odd in the genus described here. In order to ascertain the identity of this seta, the immature stages were observed. JV 5 is already present in the larval stage and JV 4 only appears in the deutonymphal stage (
Chant, 1993
). Unfortunately, the available larvae and protonymphs were not in adequate condition to be evaluated, and it was not possible to discern whether JV 5 was or was not present. In the deutonymph, a seta was clearly observed in the region normally occupied by JV 4 . Because JV 5 is present in all known phytoseiid species, we conclude that JV 5 is present in deutonymphs and adults of the new species here described and that JV 4 is absent.
